speakers.name: IPR Cell
speakers.about: IPR Cell was established in SP-IT in 2012 to protect the invention of students and faculty.The Intellectual Property Rights Cell(IPR Cell) at campus is formed to provide guidance, support and resources to all campus personnel and facilitates protection and deployment of intellectual property. IPR-Cell conducts workshops to enhance awareness on related issues, it also provides templates and guidelines for the contracts, agreements and MOUs governing the effective exploitation of the IP produced by faculties and students.

speakers.name: Enactus
speakers.about: Enactus is an international non-profit organization of students present in over 1730 campuses, spread across 39 countries and has over 72,000 students as active members who make an impact in the community, not in the form of charity, but by using the positive power of entrepreneurship. We are Enactus S.P.I.T., the student chapter of Enactus India at Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan's Sardar Patel Institute of Technology, Andheri (W), Mumbai.
